title: AWS: Costs and Usage per Service
agents: aws
catalog: cloud/aws
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check gives an overview over the unblended costs of each service
 configured in AWS accounts and shows the costs of the last day.

 To make this check work you have to configure the related special agent
 {Amazon Web Services (AWS)}.

 You can configure upper levels for {WARN}/{CRIT} (no default levels are set).

 The service goes {WARN}/{CRIT} if the costs exceed these levels.

item:
 Service name

discovery:
 One service is created for each AWS service.
